content: For the US federal services segment, revenue increased 6.2%, to $618 million, driven primarily by volume growth, tied to strong demand in the segments clinical services business and anticipated higher revenue on a large cost plus contract. On behalf of the State agency, as well as providing helpline assistance and Medicaid LTSS application support, this win with a total contract value or TCV of $129 million over a four year base period, demonstrates our ability to successfully expand into adjacent service areas with longtime customers, as program policy and needs evolve.
